- VSCode Version: Code 1.12.2 (19222cdc84ce72202478ba1cec5cb557b71163de, 2017-05-10T13:13:11.413Z)
- OS Version: Darwin x64 16.5.0
---
After rename a nodejs project directory from upper case to lower case, i got an warning when debugging:
```
Program path uses differently cased character as file on disk; this might result in breakpoints not being hit.
```
I think the reason is: i opened the project by click the menu "Open Recent", and the menu item use the old path.

When i open the project by the menu "Open...",  it works fine again.

The launch.json:
```
{
